        Unfazed by a congressional deal giving him only $1.3 billion for a barrier on the US-Mexico border, President Donald Trump is saying he found twenty times that much for overall border security “from other sources.”

    </div><div class="article__text text "><p>Details of the <em>&ldquo;compromise&rdquo;</em> negotiated by congressional Democrats and Republicans ahead of the February 15 deadline have not yet been made public, but information leaked to the media suggested the Democrats have offered only $1.375 billion, and explicitly prohibited a concrete wall.</p><div class="rtcode"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">....Will be getting almost $23 BILLION for Border Security. Regardless of Wall money, it is being built as we speak!</p>&mdash; Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) <a href="https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/1095469449052868610?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 12, 2019</a></blockquote><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div><p>The wall is <em>&ldquo;being built as we speak,&rdquo;</em> Trump tweeted on Tuesday evening, after being briefed on the deal by the <em>&ldquo;hard working Senator Richard Shelby,&rdquo;</em> the Alabama Republican chairing the Senate Appropriations Committee.</p><p>Between the deal and <em>&ldquo;lots of money from other sources,&rdquo;</em> Trump said, his administration will be getting <em>&ldquo;almost $23 billion&rdquo;</em> for border security, enough to fund much of the proposed border wall and other improvements intended to crack down on illegal crossings.</p><a class="read-more-big" href="/usa/451320-border-wall-deal-trump/" target="_blank">
    <span class="read-more-big__container">
        <span class="read-more-big__content">
            <span class="read-more-big__subtitle">Also on rt.com</span>
            <span class="read-more-big__title">'Bad' border deal welcomed by 'Swamp', but Trump seems unconcerned</span>
        </span>
            <span
                class="read-more-big__cover lazyload"
                                    
                                            data-bgset="
                            https://cdni.rt.com/files/2019.02/xxs/5c6336a7dda4c80c118b4582.JPG 280w,
